---
const stack = ["JavaScript / TypeScript", "React", "Lua", "Python", "SQL"];
---

<section id="about" class="scroll-mt-14">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-5 py-20 sm:px-8 sm:py-28">
    <div data-reveal class="mb-10 flex flex-wrap items-baseline gap-x-5 gap-y-2 sm:mb-14">
      <span class="font-mono text-sm text-accent">(03)</span>
      <h2 class="font-display text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-ink sm:text-6xl">
        About
      </h2>
    </div>

    <div class="grid gap-10 md:grid-cols-[1fr_16rem] md:gap-16">
      <p data-reveal class="max-w-2xl text-lg leading-relaxed text-muted sm:text-xl">
        Self-taught over a decade, professional for six years, with coursework at Neumont College
        of Computer Science. I've spent my whole career as the only engineer in the room — which
        means I work from a brief, ship without hand-holding, and build things non-engineers can
        sign off on. Currently deep in AI-assisted development: agent pipelines, automation, and
        LLM apps.
      </p>

      <div data-reveal style="--reveal-delay: 0.1s">
        <h3 class="font-mono text-xs tracking-[0.2em] text-muted uppercase">Core stack</h3>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-2.5">
          {
            stack.map((item) => (
              <li class="flex items-baseline gap-3 font-mono text-sm text-ink">
                <span aria-hidden="true" class="text-accent">
                  /
                </span>
                {item}
              </li>
            ))
          }
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
